summary: Cyrus got to talk about his crush on Jonah in the season two premiere right after his lookback in the previous episode!, Seven...
question: Cyrus got to talk about his crush on Jonah in the season two premiere right after his lookback in the previous episode!, Seven episodes into season three and they've not even mentioned TJs look back in the previously on segments. They really need to go big in either 8, 11 or 13 or what's the point. I love Tyrus and just want the chance to actually see them happy in more than one episode.
answer:
Well i mean the problem with that is, TJ isn’t a main character. Who would he talk about the look back with? As of episode 4, he really doesn’t know Andi, he barely knows Jonah, Cyrus is his crush and i think he’s still a LITTLE too unsure to go there just yet, and Buffy he’s still trying to get on the good side of. 

Then episode 6 he had the gun plot so he wasn’t about to be like ‘hey cyrus i know youre super scared and angry rn but i have a crush on you’ it kinda would have been a slap to the face for Tyrus, tbh. 

I mean there’s always a point up until the end, isn’t there? Look.  Just remember. Why tf would TJ just be in episode 13 if .. something.. wasn’t going on. A carnival? And TJ is there?With Cyrus??like cyrus invited TJ?sorry, they don’t care about the side character’s friendships THAT much. There’s always a reason those characters are involved. Amber shows up when she’s needed in the plot, to use her for some degree. Sure we love her and we want to see more of her, but with 7 main characters, they simply don’t have the time to develop her or TJ, just because they want to. There’s always a reason they’re in a plot. 

 And ep 11 for that, too. Where Cyrus has another BIG plot with something bad happening.  And TJ is there for him? I mean??? They definitely could have used Buffy or Andi for a funeral plot, like, friendship that’s the main root of this show. But no, it’s TJ. i mean,,, that says something. 

8 I won’t speculate too hard on because, well, maybe ep 7 leaves us still a little rocky and they have him in 8 to kinda, further smooth things over with the aftermath of the gun situation so, okay, that’s why. but also like,, theyre GOOD in that episode. You will see them happy there, i promise you that. They’re being cute and playing ping pong. We will get that happiness. i can 100% guarantee you of that, if nothing else.
